Description: Concave lip, thickened at rim, and handle sherd of Attic black-glazed pottery cup, type C; lip offset inside and outside; handles rising slightly above the level of rim; glazed black on interior and exterior; handle panel and inner sides of handles reserved with miltos wash; patchily glazed under handle. Graffito on wall.
Curator's comments: The text shows that the piece is from the same cup as 1888,0601.212, which has a dedication to (Aphrodite P)andemos. The clay is unusually light for Attic and the use of miltos unusual at this period.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1590)
